#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.46"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.46:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.46:0.2"
msgid "5. Dhammikavagga"
msgstr "5. About Dhammika"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.46:0.3"
msgid "46. Mahācundasutta"
msgstr "46. By Mahācunda"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.355"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "an6.46:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
#. VAR: sayaṃjātiyaṃ → sahajātiyaṃ (bj, pts1) | sañjātiyaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an6.46:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahācundo cetīsu viharati sayaṃjātiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Mahācunda was staying in the land of the Cetis at "
"Sahajāti."

msgctxt "an6.46:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā mahācundo bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There he addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.46:1.4"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an6.46:1.5"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahācundassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "an6.46:1.6"
msgid "Āyasmā mahācundo etadavoca:"
msgstr "Venerable Mahācunda said this:"

# See my essay on these terms and the interpretation of this sutta: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/was-there-a-conflict-between-scholars-and-meditators/2676
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.46:2.1"
msgid "“Idhāvuso, dhammayogā bhikkhū jhāyī bhikkhū apasādenti:"
msgstr ""
"“Take a case where mendicants who practice discernment of principles rebuke "
"mendicants who practice absorption meditation:"

#. VAR: nijjhāyanti avajjhāyanti → etthantare pāṭho sī, syā1-3, pā1 potthakesu natthi; nijjhāyanti apajjhāyanti (9M:1740)
msgctxt "an6.46:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘ime pana jhāyinomhā, jhāyinomhāti jhāyanti pajjhāyanti nijjhāyanti "
"avajjhāyanti."
msgstr ""
"‘They say, “We practice absorption! We practice absorption!” And they "
"meditate and concentrate and contemplate and ruminate."

#. VAR: Kimime → kintime (bj) | kiñhime (s1-3) | kiṃ hime (km, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.46:2.3"
msgid "Kimime jhāyanti, kintime jhāyanti, kathaṃ ime jhāyantī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"Why do they practice absorption meditation? In what way do they practice "
"absorption meditation? How do they practice absorption meditation?’"

msgctxt "an6.46:2.4"
msgid ""
"Tattha dhammayogā ca bhikkhū nappasīdanti, jhāyī ca bhikkhū nappasīdanti, na "
"ca bahujanahitāya paṭipannā honti bahujanasukhāya bahuno janassa atthāya "
"hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ. (1)"
msgstr ""
"In this case the mendicants who practice discernment of principles are not "
"inspired, and the mendicants who practice absorption meditation are not "
"inspired. And they’re not acting for the welfare and happiness of the "
"people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.46:3.1"
msgid "Idha panāvuso, jhāyī bhikkhū dhammayoge bhikkhū apasādenti:"
msgstr ""
"Now, take a case where mendicants who practice absorption meditation rebuke "
"mendicants who practice discernment of principles:"

msgctxt "an6.46:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘ime pana dhammayogamhā, dhammayogamhāti uddhatā unnaḷā capalā mukharā "
"vikiṇṇavācā muṭṭhassatī asampajānā asamāhitā vibbhantacittā pākatindriyā."
msgstr ""
"‘They say, “We practice discernment of principles! We practice discernment "
"of principles!” But they’re restless, insolent, fickle, gossipy, loose-"
"tongued, unmindful, lacking situational awareness and immersion, with "
"straying minds and undisciplined faculties."

msgctxt "an6.46:3.3"
msgid "Kimime dhammayogā, kintime dhammayogā, kathaṃ ime dhammayogā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"Why do they practice discernment of principles? In what way do they practice "
"discernment of principles? How do they practice discernment of principles?’"

msgctxt "an6.46:3.4"
msgid ""
"Tattha jhāyī ca bhikkhū nappasīdanti, dhammayogā ca bhikkhū nappasīdanti, na "
"ca bahujanahitāya paṭipannā honti bahujanasukhāya bahuno janassa atthāya "
"hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ. (2)"
msgstr ""
"In this case the mendicants who practice absorption meditation are not "
"inspired, and the mendicants who practice discernment of principles are not "
"inspired. And they’re not acting for the welfare and happiness of the "
"people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.356"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.46:4.1"
msgid ""
"Idha panāvuso, dhammayogā bhikkhū dhammayogānaññeva bhikkhūnaṃ vaṇṇaṃ "
"bhāsanti, no jhāyīnaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti."
msgstr ""
"Now, take a case where mendicants who practice discernment of principles "
"praise only others like them, not mendicants who practice absorption "
"meditation."

msgctxt "an6.46:4.2"
msgid ""
"Tattha dhammayogā ca bhikkhū nappasīdanti, jhāyī ca bhikkhū nappasīdanti, na "
"ca bahujanahitāya paṭipannā honti bahujanasukhāya bahuno janassa atthāya "
"hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ. (3)"
msgstr ""
"In this case the mendicants who practice discernment of principles are not "
"inspired, and the mendicants who practice absorption meditation are not "
"inspired. And they’re not acting for the welfare and happiness of the "
"people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.46:5.1"
msgid ""
"Idha panāvuso, jhāyī bhikkhū jhāyīnaññeva bhikkhūnaṃ vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti, no "
"dhammayogānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti."
msgstr ""
"And take a case where mendicants who practice absorption meditation praise "
"only others like them, not mendicants who practice discernment of principles."

msgctxt "an6.46:5.2"
msgid ""
"Tattha jhāyī ca bhikkhū nappasīdanti, dhammayogā ca bhikkhū nappasīdanti, na "
"ca bahujanahitāya paṭipannā honti bahujanasukhāya bahuno janassa atthāya "
"hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ. (4)"
msgstr ""
"In this case the mendicants who practice absorption meditation are not "
"inspired, and the mendicants who practice discernment of principles are not "
"inspired. And they’re not acting for the welfare and happiness of the "
"people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.46:6.1"
msgid "Tasmātihāvuso, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

msgctxt "an6.46:6.2"
msgid "‘dhammayogā samānā jhāyīnaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘As mendicants who practice discernment of principles, we will praise "
"mendicants who practice absorption meditation.’"

msgctxt "an6.46:6.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, āvuso, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how you should train."

msgctxt "an6.46:6.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an6.46:6.5"
msgid ""
"Acchariyā hete, āvuso, puggalā dullabhā lokasmiṃ, ye amataṃ dhātuṃ kāyena "
"phusitvā viharanti. (5)"
msgstr ""
"Because it’s incredibly rare to find individuals in the world who have "
"direct meditative experience of the deathless."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.46:7.1"
msgid "Tasmātihāvuso, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

msgctxt "an6.46:7.2"
msgid "‘jhāyī samānā dhammayogānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘As mendicants who practice absorption meditation, we will praise mendicants "
"who practice discernment of principles.’"

msgctxt "an6.46:7.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, āvuso, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how you should train."

msgctxt "an6.46:7.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an6.46:7.5"
msgid ""
"Acchariyā hete, āvuso, puggalā dullabhā lokasmiṃ ye gambhīraṃ atthapadaṃ "
"paññāya ativijjha passantī”ti. (6)"
msgstr ""
"Because it’s incredibly rare to find individuals in the world who see the "
"meaning of a deep saying with penetrating wisdom.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.46:7.6"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
